%>
<div id="sensium-details" class="project-details-section">
  <h2>Sensium Details</h2>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <div class="card-section">
    <div class="card card-full-width sensium-hero">
      <h3>Sensium: Blind-Tasting Coach</h3>
      <p class="sensium-tagline">Blind tasting, faster.</p>
      <div class="image-grid">
        <% [
          ["store_01_train_home.png", "Train"],
          ["store_04_grape_detail_scan_first.png", "Dossier"],
          ["store_05_compare_fast_call.png", "Compare"]
        ].each do |img, cap| %>
          <div class="image-wrapper">
            <img src="<%= asset_path("project/sensium/iphone/#{img}") %>" alt="Sensium — <%= cap %>" class="sensium-image sensium-image-large" loading="lazy" decoding="async">
          </div>
        <% end %>
      </div>
      <p>Sensium is a premium blind-tasting coach for sommelier-track students, exam candidates, and serious enthusiasts who want sharper grape calls under pressure — without carrying an encyclopedia in their pocket. The product is built around four decision-first surfaces: <strong>Train</strong> your palate with daily drills, browse scan-first <strong>Grape</strong> dossiers, <strong>Compare</strong> confusing pairs for the one cue that splits them, and reason through a <strong>Blind</strong> tasting to a ranked, defendable shortlist. A single Kotlin Multiplatform core drives a true cross-platform suite, all offline-first, with one consistent warm-garnet design language across every screen.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Highlights -->
  <div class="sensium-highlights">
    <div class="sensium-stat"><span class="sensium-stat-num">1,534</span><span class="sensium-stat-label">grape varieties</span></div>
    <div class="sensium-stat"><span class="sensium-stat-num">4</span><span class="sensium-stat-label">study modes</span></div>
    <div class="sensium-stat"><span class="sensium-stat-num">10</span><span class="sensium-stat-label">platforms</span></div>
    <div class="sensium-stat"><span class="sensium-stat-num"><i class="fa-solid fa-plane-up"></i></span><span class="sensium-stat-label">offline-first</span></div>
    <div class="sensium-stat"><span class="sensium-stat-num"><i class="fa-solid fa-shield-halved"></i></span><span class="sensium-stat-label">no ads, no tracking</span></div>
    <div class="sensium-stat"><span class="sensium-stat-num"><i class="fa-solid fa-rotate"></i></span><span class="sensium-stat-label">one premium, every device</span></div>
  </div>

  <!-- Platform reach -->
  <div class="card-section">
    <div class="card card-full-width sensium-platform-card">
      <h3>One brain, every screen</h3>
      <div class="sensium-platform-strip">
        <span class="sensium-platform"><i class="fa-brands fa-apple"></i> iPhone</span>
        <span class="sensium-platform"><i class="fa-solid fa-tablet-screen-button"></i> iPad</span>
        <span class="sensium-platform"><i class="fa-solid fa-desktop"></i> Mac</span>
        <span class="sensium-platform"><i class="fa-solid fa-clock"></i> Apple Watch</span>
        <span class="sensium-platform"><i class="fa-solid fa-vr-cardboard"></i> Apple Vision Pro</span>
        <span class="sensium-platform"><i class="fa-brands fa-android"></i> Android</span>
        <span class="sensium-platform"><i class="fa-solid fa-tablet-screen-button"></i> Android Tablet</span>
        <span class="sensium-platform"><i class="fa-solid fa-clock"></i> Wear OS</span>
        <span class="sensium-platform"><i class="fa-brands fa-chrome"></i> Chromebook</span>
        <span class="sensium-platform"><i class="fa-solid fa-globe"></i> Web / PWA</span>
      </div>
      <p>A single Kotlin Multiplatform shared module holds the data model, repository, search, and the blind-scoring engine — so every platform speaks the same language and ranks grapes identically. Native shells (SwiftUI across Apple platforms, Jetpack Compose on Android and Wear OS, and a static web export) keep each experience fast and at home on its device. Store launches are rolling out over the coming weeks.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- The Four Pillars -->
  <h3 class="section-title">The Four Pillars</h3>

  <div class="card-section">
    <div class="card">
      <h3>Train — build the skill</h3>
      <div class="image-grid">
        <% [
          ["store_01_train_home.png", "Daily blind-tasting drills"],
          ["store_02_train_active_recall.png", "Reveal, grade, reinforce"],
          ["store_11_train_keep_going.png", "Keep the streak alive"]
        ].each do |img, cap| %>
          <div class="image-wrapper">
            <img src="<%= asset_path("project/sensium/iphone/#{img}") %>" alt="Sensium Train — <%= cap %>" class="sensium-image" loading="lazy" decoding="async">
            <span class="sensium-caption"><%= cap %></span>
          </div>
        <% end %>
      </div>
      <p>Five focused minutes a day. Confusion-pair drills ("Riesling or Grüner — what tells them apart?") run as adaptive multiple-choice, active recall, or auto-mix. Reveal an answer, self-grade with Got it / Again, and every miss is queued for tomorrow. A local streak counter keeps you honest — no account, no nagging.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>Grapes — understand the tell</h3>
      <div class="image-grid">
        <% [
          ["store_03_grapes_search_recent.png", "Search; focus to your Top 5 / 10 / 25 / 50"],
          ["store_04_grape_detail_scan_first.png", "Scan-first dossier with confusion cues"]
        ].each do |img, cap| %>
          <div class="image-wrapper">
            <img src="<%= asset_path("project/sensium/iphone/#{img}") %>" alt="Sensium Grapes — <%= cap %>" class="sensium-image" loading="lazy" decoding="async">
            <span class="sensium-caption"><%= cap %></span>
          </div>
        <% end %>
      </div>
      <p>A searchable atlas of 1,534 varieties that you can narrow to the most-tested grapes. Every dossier opens with the highest-signal cues first — color pill, signature aromas, blind tell, and fast separator — followed by "Most Confused With" sub-cards that spell out exactly why two grapes get mistaken and what to look for instead.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card-section">
    <div class="card">
      <h3>Compare — separate close calls</h3>
      <div class="image-grid">
        <div class="image-wrapper">
          <img src="<%= asset_path('project/sensium/iphone/store_05_compare_fast_call.png') %>" alt="Sensium Compare — Fast Call decision rule" class="sensium-image sensium-image-large" loading="lazy" decoding="async">
          <span class="sensium-caption">Fast Call: the single best decision rule</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p>A top-level separation workspace for the pairs that trip people up. Pick any two grapes and get a Fast Call panel that names the single best decision rule, side-by-side structure pillars (color, acidity, tannin, body, alcohol, oak, aromas), and an overlap-vs-differences read — with a one-tap "Train this pair" that drops you straight into drills filtered to your problem grapes.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>Blind — check your reasoning</h3>
      <div class="image-grid">
        <% [
          ["store_06_blind_coach_tools.png", "Coach tools hub"],
          ["store_07_blind_aroma_learning.png", "Aroma → grape"],
          ["store_08_blind_process_learning.png", "Winemaking process glossary"],
          ["store_09_blind_region_learning.png", "Region narrowing"]
        ].each do |img, cap| %>
          <div class="image-wrapper">
            <img src="<%= asset_path("project/sensium/iphone/#{img}") %>" alt="Sensium Blind — <%= cap %>" class="sensium-image" loading="lazy" decoding="async">
            <span class="sensium-caption"><%= cap %></span>
          </div>
        <% end %>
      </div>
      <p>Reframed from "identify for me" to "check my reasoning." Log your structure read and aroma evidence to get a ranked shortlist of likely grapes with a rationale you can defend — backed by mismatch-sensitive scoring, confidence buckets, and explicit "separate these by…" guidance on close calls. Coach quizzes (Aroma → grape, Process glossary, Region narrowing) drill the upstream skills that make blind calls actually work.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Beyond the daily loop -->
  <h3 class="section-title">Beyond the Daily Loop</h3>

  <div class="card-section">
    <div class="card">
      <h3>SAT Rebuild &amp; Exam Mode</h3>
      <div class="image-grid sensium-wide-grid">
        <div class="image-wrapper">
          <img src="<%= asset_path('project/sensium/mac/mac_09_sat_rebuild.png') %>" alt="Sensium SAT Rebuild" class="sensium-image sensium-image-wide" loading="lazy" decoding="async">
          <span class="sensium-caption">SAT Rebuild — reconstruct a full profile</span>
        </div>
        <div class="image-wrapper">
          <img src="<%= asset_path('project/sensium/mac/mac_10_exam.png') %>" alt="Sensium Exam Mode" class="sensium-image sensium-image-wide" loading="lazy" decoding="async">
          <span class="sensium-caption">Exam Mode — timed sessions</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p>SAT Rebuild challenges put you in front of a target grape and ask you to reconstruct its full profile — color, structure, signature aromas, classic anchors — at Foundation, Classic, or Expert difficulty. Timed Exam Mode and Mistake Replay (drills tuned to your own confusion pairs) turn weaknesses into a personalized practice plan.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>Premium &amp; account</h3>
      <div class="image-grid">
        <div class="image-wrapper">
          <img src="<%= asset_path('project/sensium/iphone/store_10_paywall.png') %>" alt="Sensium Premium paywall" class="sensium-image" loading="lazy" decoding="async">
          <span class="sensium-caption">One purchase, every device</span>
        </div>
        <div class="image-wrapper">
          <img src="<%= asset_path('project/sensium/mac/mac_13_account.png') %>" alt="Sensium account and sync" class="sensium-image sensium-image-wide" loading="lazy" decoding="async">
          <span class="sensium-caption">Optional account + cross-device sync</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p>The free tier keeps the daily loop running with the full catalog. Premium ($8.99/mo or $59.99/yr) unlocks unlimited Blind rankings, unlimited Coach quizzes, SAT Rebuild, Exam Mode, Coach Memory sync, and Mistake Replay — unified across iOS, Android, and web by RevenueCat, so you buy once and restore everywhere. Sign-in (Apple, Google, or email) is optional and only powers cloud sync.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

