  <!-- Under the hood -->
  <h3 class="section-title">Under the Hood</h3>

  <div class="card-section">
    <div class="card card-full-width">
      <h3>Architecture &amp; engineering</h3>
      <div class="image-grid sensium-wide-grid">
        <div class="image-wrapper">
          <img src="<%= asset_path('project/sensium/feature_graphic_vineyard.png') %>" alt="Sensium — from vine to glass, know every grape" class="sensium-image sensium-image-wide" loading="lazy" decoding="async">
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="sensium-tech-tags">
        <span class="sensium-tech-tag">Kotlin Multiplatform</span>
        <span class="sensium-tech-tag">SwiftUI</span>
        <span class="sensium-tech-tag">Jetpack Compose</span>
        <span class="sensium-tech-tag">RealityKit (visionOS)</span>
        <span class="sensium-tech-tag">Firebase</span>
        <span class="sensium-tech-tag">RevenueCat</span>
        <span class="sensium-tech-tag">Stripe (web)</span>
        <span class="sensium-tech-tag">Next.js / PWA</span>
        <span class="sensium-tech-tag">Gradle · XcodeGen</span>
        <span class="sensium-tech-tag">Python QA pipeline</span>
        <span class="sensium-tech-tag">Multi-platform CI</span>
      </div>
      <p>One Kotlin Multiplatform shared core (data model, repository, search, and the blind-scoring engine) is consumed by SwiftUI (iOS / iPadOS / macOS / visionOS / watchOS) and Jetpack Compose (Android / Wear OS), plus a static web export served on Firebase Hosting at <a href="https://sensium.wine" target="_blank">sensium.wine</a>. It's backed by Firebase (Auth, Firestore, Functions, Remote Config) with an offline-first local JSON catalog, unified subscriptions via RevenueCat with a Stripe web checkout lane, and a strict Python data-validation &amp; QA pipeline (schema, editorial, duplicate, and design-token contrast checks). Multi-platform CI (Gradle, XcodeGen, SwiftLint, Detekt) keeps every target green — no ads, no third-party tracking SDKs, and consent-gated analytics throughout.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="navigation-buttons">
